The marshals just did and he's

750
00:33:01.352 --> 00:33:02.587
<i>on his way to you as we speak.</i>

751
00:33:02.653 --> 00:33:03.921
Okay. We'll get back to you.

752
00:33:03.988 --> 00:33:05.022
We're standing by.

753
00:33:05.122 --> 00:33:06.323
We need to get Voit

754
00:33:06.457 --> 00:33:08.393
to face the fact
that if he doesn't come clean.

755
00:33:08.493 --> 00:33:10.094
the real killer
gets away with this.

756
00:33:10.160 --> 00:33:12.897
- Let me talk to him.
- No. JJ. let me?

757
00:33:17.568 --> 00:33:19.169
(door opens)

758
00:33:22.172 --> 00:33:23.173
(sighs)

759
00:33:23.273 --> 00:33:25.275
(door closes)

760
00:33:30.347 --> 00:33:31.849
(sighs)

761
00:33:31.949 --> 00:33:34.685
Hell of a performance today.

762
00:33:36.654 --> 00:33:38.188
Why are you here?

763
00:33:38.989 --> 00:33:40.625
I know you want
the state of North Carolina

764
00:33:40.725 --> 00:33:42.927
to find you guilty
and put you to death.

765
00:33:43.027 --> 00:33:46.196
And I-I swear.
I wish they were gonna do it.

766
00:33:46.296 --> 00:33:48.733
But the problem is that means
the person or persons

767
00:33:48.833 --> 00:33:50.234
who are actually responsible

768
00:33:50.334 --> 00:33:52.570
for killing Kaliyah
and Avery Burke

769
00:33:52.703 --> 00:33:53.804
will escape justice.

770
00:33:53.871 --> 00:33:56.006
Yeah. Tyler.
you don't know shit.

771
00:33:57.141 --> 00:33:59.610
Be serious.
Your team figured this out.

772
00:33:59.710 --> 00:34:01.579
If it were up to you
and D.A. Joy.

773
00:34:01.712 --> 00:34:04.348
the report on the Haeberlin case
would be buried

774
00:34:04.449 --> 00:34:07.217
and Tristan Burke and Elias Voit

775
00:34:07.317 --> 00:34:10.320
would be on trial
for capital murder conspiracy.

776
00:34:10.421 --> 00:34:13.791
Hey. you need to tell the locals
exactly what's going on here.

777
00:34:15.493 --> 00:34:18.596
You do realize that if I hadn't
agreed to indulge all this.

778
00:34:18.729 --> 00:34:22.433
then Kaliyah's body would never
have been found. right?

779
00:34:22.533 --> 00:34:24.569
And nobody

780
00:34:24.669 --> 00:34:27.037
ever would have paid
for her death. so...

781
00:34:27.104 --> 00:34:29.073
(snorts softly)

782
00:34:29.173 --> 00:34:31.942
- ...better Sicarius than nobody.
- You can change that.

783
00:34:32.076 --> 00:34:33.644
Yeah. and you can do your job.

784
00:34:35.045 --> 00:34:36.881
You can try
reading the case file.

785
00:34:36.947 --> 00:34:39.416
because everything you need to
figure this out is right there.

786
00:34:39.550 --> 00:34:41.686
But if you can't do that...

787
00:34:41.752 --> 00:34:44.555
if you can't figure it out...

788
00:34:44.622 --> 00:34:47.958
then Sicarius
will die for your sins.

789
00:34:50.861 --> 00:34:53.130
TRISTAN:
I swear to God. (chuckles)

790
00:34:53.263 --> 00:34:55.165
as soon as this shit is over.
I'm suing the fuck

791
00:34:55.265 --> 00:34:58.202
out of lame-ass Joy
and you F-B-fucking-I's.

792
00:34:58.268 --> 00:35:00.170
You watch.
(short chortle)

793
00:35:00.270 --> 00:35:03.307
- All right.
- Yeah. well. get in line.

794
00:35:04.141 --> 00:35:05.743
This shit is funny to you?

795
00:35:05.810 --> 00:35:07.111
Listen to me.

796
00:35:07.244 --> 00:35:08.779
If you hadn't been
fucking around

797
00:35:08.913 --> 00:35:11.248
and lying to the cops. we
wouldn't even be here right now.

798
00:35:11.315 --> 00:35:12.650
Your goddamn DNA

799
00:35:12.783 --> 00:35:14.619
is all over those bins
along with Kaliyah's body.

800
00:35:14.752 --> 00:35:16.787
Yeah. okay.
because they're mine.

801
00:35:16.921 --> 00:35:17.822
So what?

802
00:35:17.955 --> 00:35:19.490
I used them to move all my shit

803
00:35:19.590 --> 00:35:21.158
into K's house
when we got married.

804
00:35:21.291 --> 00:35:22.793
- They been in the basement.
- So what?

805
00:35:22.893 --> 00:35:25.763
So the killer stole them
along with Kaliyah and Avery?

806
00:35:25.830 --> 00:35:29.066
I don't know.
It seems that way. right?

807
00:35:30.635 --> 00:35:32.537
Tell me something. Tristan.

808
00:35:33.437 --> 00:35:34.705
What?

809
00:35:35.540 --> 00:35:37.407
Why did you get married?

810
00:35:42.146 --> 00:35:44.081
'Cause Kaliyah got pregnant.

811
00:35:44.148 --> 00:35:46.283
And to be honest.

812
00:35:46.350 --> 00:35:49.153
I told her I would pay
to take care of it.

813
00:35:49.286 --> 00:35:51.355
but she wasn't hearing
any of that.

814
00:35:51.455 --> 00:35:52.823
Of course.

815
00:35:52.923 --> 00:35:55.092
(sighs)

816
00:35:55.159 --> 00:35:57.695
And then my mom found out.

817
00:35:57.795 --> 00:35:59.997
So I had to do right.
(soft chuckle)

818
00:36:00.130 --> 00:36:02.667
You don't even know
how many times

819
00:36:02.767 --> 00:36:06.370
I actually prayed to be free.

820
00:36:07.304 --> 00:36:09.774
And so your prayers
were answered.

821
00:36:09.874 --> 00:36:11.842
No.

822
00:36:14.311 --> 00:36:16.881
Look. I know
I'm not a good guy...

823
00:36:17.682 --> 00:36:19.516
...but I swear to God...

824
00:36:20.350 --> 00:36:22.452
...I'm not a bad guy. either.

825
00:36:29.159 --> 00:36:30.795
GREEN:
Honestly?

826
00:36:30.861 --> 00:36:33.664
I'm not sure what the hell
I'm looking at here.

827
00:36:33.764 --> 00:36:35.399
Assuming what you said before...

828
00:36:35.532 --> 00:36:37.702
that this is a crime of passion.
not psychopathy...

829
00:36:37.835 --> 00:36:39.970
then that motive
still lands hard on Tristan.

830
00:36:40.037 --> 00:36:41.639
ROSSI:
Because that's what the real killer

831
00:36:41.706 --> 00:36:43.608
was banking on from the start.

832
00:36:43.708 --> 00:36:46.877
So. let's think harder
about this disposal site.

833
00:36:46.977 --> 00:36:48.879
It's remote.
which means whoever chose it

834
00:36:48.979 --> 00:36:51.348
had to have had
a lot of experience there.

835
00:36:51.415 --> 00:36:52.717
Years.

836
00:36:52.850 --> 00:36:54.151
JJ:
That's not Tristan.

837
00:36:54.251 --> 00:36:56.987
He only moved here
when he married Kaliyah.

838
00:36:57.054 --> 00:36:58.388
He's also not the nature type.

839
00:36:58.522 --> 00:37:02.159
So. if "crime of passion."
then "real killer"

840
00:37:02.226 --> 00:37:04.762
must be someone with an intimate
knowledge of Yasper Creek.

841
00:37:04.895 --> 00:37:08.432
and presumably as close
to Kaliyah. emotionally.

842
00:37:08.532 --> 00:37:10.000
as her own husband.

843
00:37:10.067 --> 00:37:12.970
It's-it's got to be
a family member.

844
00:37:13.070 --> 00:37:14.004
No way.

845
00:37:14.071 --> 00:37:15.272
Come on. we've seen how much

846
00:37:15.372 --> 00:37:16.641
the loss of Kaliyah
and her daughter

847
00:37:16.741 --> 00:37:18.508
has wrecked
her surviving family.

848
00:37:18.609 --> 00:37:20.244
PRENTISS:
I know. But we need

849
00:37:20.344 --> 00:37:22.012
to have Garcia look
into their backgrounds.

850
00:37:22.112 --> 00:37:23.447
(line ringing)

851
00:37:23.547 --> 00:37:25.482
<i>(knocking on door)</i>

852
00:37:29.286 --> 00:37:32.022
Hello. Mr. Faust. We're sorry
to trouble you at this hour.

853
00:37:32.122 --> 00:37:34.659
Uh. no. no. Please. come on in.

854
00:37:34.759 --> 00:37:36.827
Ryleigh's right down there.

855
00:37:41.999 --> 00:37:43.533
D.A. Joy just called.

856
00:37:43.634 --> 00:37:46.036
- We're very sorry.
- (exhales)

857
00:37:46.103 --> 00:37:48.873
Well. at least
she's coming home.

858
00:37:48.939 --> 00:37:50.440
How may we help you?

859
00:37:50.540 --> 00:37:52.276
We need to speak to Jesse.

860
00:37:52.376 --> 00:37:53.543
JESSE:
Me?

861
00:37:53.644 --> 00:37:54.645
W-What for?

862
00:37:54.745 --> 00:37:56.280
Maybe you want to come with us.

863
00:37:56.380 --> 00:37:57.481
Are you serious?

864
00:37:57.614 --> 00:37:59.950
- What's going on?
- Nothing's going on.

865
00:38:04.454 --> 00:38:05.756
Jesse.

866
00:38:09.794 --> 00:38:11.528
- (glass clattering)
- (dog barking)

867
00:38:15.800 --> 00:38:17.367
(grunting)

868
00:38:18.535 --> 00:38:19.737
JESSE:
You don't understand!

869
00:38:19.804 --> 00:38:22.707
- No. I don't.
- (handcuffs click)

870
00:38:28.846 --> 00:38:30.347
(door opens. closes)

871
00:38:31.048 --> 00:38:32.549
JJ:
Jesse Poole.

872
00:38:32.649 --> 00:38:35.886
Age 37. born and raised
here in Friars Town.

873
00:38:35.986 --> 00:38:39.356
Carpenter by trade.
but a longtime volunteer

874
00:38:39.456 --> 00:38:40.925
for the forestry service.

875
00:38:41.025 --> 00:38:45.062
Spent a lot of time
around Yasper.

876
00:38:45.930 --> 00:38:47.364
It's not what you think.

877
00:38:47.464 --> 00:38:49.767
What do we think. Jesse?

878
00:38:49.867 --> 00:38:53.137
I... I don't know.

879
00:38:54.004 --> 00:38:55.505
Why'd you run?

880
00:38:55.572 --> 00:38:57.674
I... I...

881
00:38:57.775 --> 00:38:59.643
I'm allowed a lawyer.

882
00:39:02.880 --> 00:39:04.581
Yes. Yes. you are.

883
00:39:05.783 --> 00:39:07.752
We'll have you wait right here.

884
00:39:10.955 --> 00:39:12.757
(door opens)

885
00:39:14.624 --> 00:39:15.926
(door closes)

886
00:39:16.026 --> 00:39:17.394
(door opens)

887
00:39:17.461 --> 00:39:18.929
♪ ♪

888
00:39:19.063 --> 00:39:21.231
(chains clinking)

889
00:39:21.331 --> 00:39:23.133
(door closes)

890
00:39:25.269 --> 00:39:27.171
JESSE:
No. No.

891
00:39:27.938 --> 00:39:29.940
Hey. what the actual fuck. huh?

892
00:39:30.040 --> 00:39:31.275
(door closes)

893
00:39:31.408 --> 00:39:33.577
You can't leave me here
with this psycho.

894
00:39:33.677 --> 00:39:35.012
Can you hear me?

895
00:39:35.112 --> 00:39:36.413
Hello?

896
00:39:36.480 --> 00:39:37.547
- Hey!
- You think this'll work?

897
00:39:37.614 --> 00:39:39.116
- Hey! What the fuck?
- Well.

898
00:39:39.249 --> 00:39:41.551
it's not the craziest idea
Rossi's ever come up with.

899
00:39:41.618 --> 00:39:44.454
JESSE: I want my lawyer.
Get me a fucking lawyer!

900
00:39:47.758 --> 00:39:50.027
D.A. Joy.
I need to talk to you.

901
00:39:50.127 --> 00:39:51.495
PRENTISS:
Mrs. Poole. we understand

902
00:39:51.628 --> 00:39:53.130
- how confusing this...
- You can't possible think

903
00:39:53.263 --> 00:39:55.465
my husband had anything to do
with my sister's murder.

904
00:39:55.565 --> 00:39:56.500
We do.

905
00:39:56.600 --> 00:39:59.103
Please.

906
00:40:03.240 --> 00:40:05.409
My husband is a good man.

907
00:40:05.509 --> 00:40:07.511
L-Look. Jesse just
couldn't hurt a soul.

908
00:40:07.644 --> 00:40:10.114
Now. if-if you don't think
this Sicarius person

909
00:40:10.214 --> 00:40:11.581
is guilty. then why don't
you take another look

910
00:40:11.681 --> 00:40:12.983
- at Tristan Burke?
- ROSSI: Oh. we did.

911
00:40:13.117 --> 00:40:15.719
Somebody tried
to frame them both.

912
00:40:15.820 --> 00:40:17.021
Not Jesse.

913
00:40:17.922 --> 00:40:20.090
- Why?
- ROSSI: Yes. why?

914
00:40:20.190 --> 00:40:22.259
That is the question.

915
00:40:22.359 --> 00:40:24.161
With Jesse. right now.
we have two points

916
00:40:24.261 --> 00:40:28.132
of the conviction triangle:
opportunity and means.

917
00:40:28.232 --> 00:40:29.867
But what's his motive?
What does he stand to gain

918
00:40:30.000 --> 00:40:32.602
by a double homicide?

919
00:40:32.669 --> 00:40:34.138
PRENTISS:
The truth is.

920
00:40:34.238 --> 00:40:37.842
there are only two
fundamental motives for murder:

921
00:40:37.942 --> 00:40:39.609
passion or profit.

922
00:40:39.709 --> 00:40:42.279
Sometimes they go
hand in hand. like here.

923
00:40:42.346 --> 00:40:45.715
What? Are you gonna say
Jesse was rebuffed by my sister

924
00:40:45.850 --> 00:40:47.885
and that he has plans
to kill me. too?

925
00:40:47.985 --> 00:40:50.921
Well. actually.
your husband has no motive.

926
00:40:51.021 --> 00:40:53.790
He's been loyal to you
to a fault.

927
00:40:53.891 --> 00:40:56.060
PRENTISS: Over the years.
with the work we do.

928
00:40:56.160 --> 00:40:57.828
we've seen how the thin line

929
00:40:57.928 --> 00:41:00.130
between grief and guilt
can often blur.

930
00:41:00.230 --> 00:41:03.300
While it seems understandable
for a family member

931
00:41:03.400 --> 00:41:06.971
to try to minimize
the reminders of the deceased.

932
00:41:07.037 --> 00:41:09.339
the profile of a family member

933
00:41:09.439 --> 00:41:11.175
in mourning

934
00:41:11.275 --> 00:41:12.910
suggests it's far
more common for them

935
00:41:13.010 --> 00:41:14.912
to do just about everything

936
00:41:15.045 --> 00:41:17.181
to preserve the memories

937
00:41:17.247 --> 00:41:18.849
of their lost loved one.

938
00:41:18.949 --> 00:41:20.951
ROSSI: This house meant so much
to your sister.

939
00:41:21.051 --> 00:41:24.254
She added a lot of her own
little touches. didn't she?

940
00:41:24.388 --> 00:41:26.823
PRENTISS:
So. i-it's a bit curious to us

941
00:41:26.924 --> 00:41:29.259
that the moment
you took possession of it.

942
00:41:29.393 --> 00:41:31.095
you erased every trace of her.

943
00:41:31.195 --> 00:41:33.763
From shelves in the. uh.
living room

944
00:41:33.898 --> 00:41:36.033
to backsplash in the kitchen.

945
00:41:36.133 --> 00:41:37.234
How dare you?

946
00:41:37.334 --> 00:41:39.036
Where-where you going
with this?

947
00:41:39.136 --> 00:41:40.604
Mr. Faust.

948
00:41:40.737 --> 00:41:43.507
do you know the reason
why your wife

949
00:41:43.607 --> 00:41:46.376
left her grandparents' house
to Kaliyah

950
00:41:46.476 --> 00:41:48.913
and not to both your daughters?

951
00:41:49.013 --> 00:41:50.847
Well-well.
that was just some...

952
00:41:51.715 --> 00:41:54.451
I-I mean.
it-it doesn't mean anything.

953
00:41:54.551 --> 00:41:56.453
"And in the event
of Kaliyah's death.

954
00:41:56.553 --> 00:41:58.923
the house would belong
to Avery..."

955
00:41:59.023 --> 00:42:01.091
Now you say what you want to say
or you better shut the fuck up.

956
00:42:01.191 --> 00:42:03.961
Passion and profit. Ryleigh.

957
00:42:05.029 --> 00:42:07.932
Your husband is in that
back room spilling his guts.

958
00:42:08.065 --> 00:42:10.968
You tell us
what he's got to say.

959
00:42:11.101 --> 00:42:14.138
He helped you murder
your own sister

960
00:42:14.271 --> 00:42:16.373
and your precious little niece.

961
00:42:16.440 --> 00:42:18.408
- No. no. No.
- PRENTISS: You and Jesse

962
00:42:18.475 --> 00:42:19.476
tried to frame Tristan.

963
00:42:19.576 --> 00:42:20.945
And once you realized that lie

964
00:42:21.045 --> 00:42:22.446
wasn't gonna hold... I'm guessing

965
00:42:22.579 --> 00:42:24.581
you were the one
who was listening

966
00:42:24.648 --> 00:42:26.116
to a popular podcast...

967
00:42:26.216 --> 00:42:28.785
you thought maybe a true crime
twist might save you.

968
00:42:28.919 --> 00:42:30.988
That's why you planted
the Haeberlin case.

969
00:42:31.088 --> 00:42:32.856
(door opens)

970
00:42:38.862 --> 00:42:41.098
You goddamn...
You dumb son of a bitch!

971
00:42:41.165 --> 00:42:42.466
ROSSI:
That's enough.

972
00:42:42.566 --> 00:42:43.867
Ryleigh. tell 'em they're wrong.

973
00:42:43.968 --> 00:42:47.071
- Tell 'em they're wrong.
- It's not fucking fair.

974
00:42:48.072 --> 00:42:50.740
Kaliyah got everything
she wanted.

975
00:42:50.840 --> 00:42:51.841
Ryleigh.

976
00:42:51.976 --> 00:42:53.843
Everything.

977
00:42:53.978 --> 00:42:57.114
And I got the scraps.

978
00:42:57.214 --> 00:42:59.316
And when Mom was dying.

979
00:42:59.416 --> 00:43:01.618
I cleaned up her shit.

980
00:43:01.685 --> 00:43:03.988
And...

981
00:43:04.088 --> 00:43:06.823
in the end. still...

982
00:43:07.791 --> 00:43:09.826
...she picked Kaliyah...

983
00:43:10.727 --> 00:43:12.662
...over me.

984
00:43:12.796 --> 00:43:15.299
Ryleigh. No...

985
00:43:21.771 --> 00:43:23.673
- Ryleigh.
- (handcuffs click)

986
00:43:23.773 --> 00:43:24.874
No.

987
00:43:27.811 --> 00:43:28.945
Thank you.

988
00:43:40.624 --> 00:43:43.127
<i>GREEN:
"Whatever is begun in anger</i>

989
00:43:43.227 --> 00:43:44.861
<i>ends in shame."</i>

990
00:43:44.961 --> 00:43:46.730
<i>Benjamin Franklin.</i>

991
00:43:49.333 --> 00:43:51.735
How you doing. kid?

992
00:43:52.769 --> 00:43:54.138
Been better.

993
00:43:55.339 --> 00:43:56.706
Want to talk about it?

994
00:43:56.806 --> 00:44:00.077
Seems like all I'm doing
is talking about it. actually.

995
00:44:00.210 --> 00:44:01.678
How's that?

996
00:44:01.745 --> 00:44:03.580
Counseling.

997
00:44:03.713 --> 00:44:06.750
You know. for years
after Alison was murdered.

998
00:44:06.850 --> 00:44:09.186
I had this one. singular focus.

999
00:44:09.286 --> 00:44:12.556
Find the man who killed her
and end him.

1000
00:44:12.656 --> 00:44:14.591
And then...

1001
00:44:16.560 --> 00:44:19.396
...my life took
this crazy-ass turn.

1002
00:44:19.496 --> 00:44:21.931
And now I'm here. but I'm...

1003
00:44:23.167 --> 00:44:25.169
...I'm at a loss.

1004
00:44:26.836 --> 00:44:28.872
- What makes you feel that?
- For starters.

1005
00:44:28.972 --> 00:44:31.441
even fucking Voit
is a better profiler than me.

1006
00:44:31.541 --> 00:44:33.110
No. I told you.
the guy's a psycho.

1007
00:44:33.243 --> 00:44:35.945
- It comes naturally to him.
- I never would have profiled

1008
00:44:36.046 --> 00:44:37.514
Ryleigh and her husband
as suspects.

1009
00:44:37.581 --> 00:44:39.449
- Never.
- Because your personal experience

1010
00:44:39.549 --> 00:44:43.253
with family is telling you
blood doesn't betray blood.

1011
00:44:43.353 --> 00:44:46.956
Obviously. it can and it does.

1012
00:44:47.057 --> 00:44:49.159
so all this means
is you need more time

1013
00:44:49.259 --> 00:44:52.496
to set aside your personal bias.

1014
00:44:53.430 --> 00:44:55.165
I see.

1015
00:44:55.265 --> 00:44:58.168
I need to detach.

1016
00:44:59.035 --> 00:45:01.971
It'll take time. And more reps.

1017
00:45:02.072 --> 00:45:04.141
What if I can't hack it?

1018
00:45:05.075 --> 00:45:06.210
You will.

1019
00:45:06.310 --> 00:45:07.977
How can you be so sure?

1020
00:45:11.448 --> 00:45:15.152
Because I'm a great
fucking profiler.

1021
00:45:23.660 --> 00:45:25.229
GARCIA: Keep 'em closed.
keep 'em closed. Okay.

1022
00:45:25.295 --> 00:45:27.831
Not yet. not yet. Okay...
Okay. you can open your eyes.

1023
00:45:27.964 --> 00:45:28.965
- What do you think?
- Wow!

1024
00:45:29.065 --> 00:45:31.568
Ah! Bringing the outdoors

1025
00:45:31.668 --> 00:45:33.870
to the indoors. I mean...

1026
00:45:33.970 --> 00:45:35.071
This is pretty cool. right?

1027
00:45:35.172 --> 00:45:37.374
You guys.
I don't know what to say.

1028
00:45:37.474 --> 00:45:38.508
Wha...

1029
00:45:38.608 --> 00:45:40.410
I don't know. it's kind of dumb.

1030
00:45:40.510 --> 00:45:42.078
Henry.

1031
00:45:42.179 --> 00:45:43.680
ALVEZ:
Kind of dumb?

1032
00:45:43.813 --> 00:45:45.282
No way. No.

1033
00:45:45.382 --> 00:45:46.650
It's not dumb. Okay?

1034
00:45:46.750 --> 00:45:48.818
I mean. we used to do this
when I was a kid.

1035
00:45:48.918 --> 00:45:50.754
and it's all about
using your imagination.

1036
00:45:50.854 --> 00:45:53.490
All right? We're gonna pretend
to sleep under the stars...

1037
00:45:53.590 --> 00:45:54.891
No. Henry. you're right.

1038
00:45:54.991 --> 00:45:56.426
It is. it's a little dumb.

1039
00:45:56.526 --> 00:45:58.928
We could've painted
florescent stars on the ceiling.

1040
00:45:59.028 --> 00:46:00.164
- That would have made sense.
- ALVEZ: No.

1041
00:46:00.264 --> 00:46:02.031
It's all good.

1042
00:46:02.132 --> 00:46:03.967
It is all good and we're gonna
have a good time

1043
00:46:04.067 --> 00:46:05.535
because we are gonna
make some s'mores.

1044
00:46:05.635 --> 00:46:08.538
We're gonna cook them
over the open stove here.

1045
00:46:08.672 --> 00:46:10.640
And it's gonna be great.
What do you say?

1046
00:46:10.740 --> 00:46:12.108
Sure. Why not?

1047
00:46:12.176 --> 00:46:13.343
That's what I'm talking about.

1048
00:46:13.477 --> 00:46:15.379
- Let's go. "Dumb."
- (phone chimes)

1049
00:46:15.479 --> 00:46:17.547
- How dare you?
- (JJ chuckles)

1050
00:46:17.681 --> 00:46:19.816
- Oh.
- ALVEZ: Here.

1051
00:46:19.883 --> 00:46:20.984
- Dumb?
- GARCIA: Oh...

1052
00:46:21.084 --> 00:46:23.220
ALVEZ:
Not so dumb.

1053
00:46:23.320 --> 00:46:25.522
Oh. my.
(exhales)

1054
00:46:25.622 --> 00:46:28.392
Ooh. Is that Mr. Saturday?

1055
00:46:28.525 --> 00:46:31.395
Yes. Uh...

1056
00:46:31.495 --> 00:46:34.231
- Got his days wrong.
- Aw.

1057
00:46:34.364 --> 00:46:36.533
Oh. well. then. you should go.

1058
00:46:36.666 --> 00:46:37.934
Absolutely not.

1059
00:46:38.034 --> 00:46:40.904
- Sisters over misters.
- Aw.

1060
00:46:41.037 --> 00:46:42.839
ALVEZ:
Watch me... watch this.

1061
00:46:43.707 --> 00:46:45.309
Whoa. Yeah.

1062
00:46:45.375 --> 00:46:47.611
Seriously. though.

1063
00:46:47.711 --> 00:46:49.713
- Thank you for this.
- Mm.

1064
00:46:49.813 --> 00:46:51.548
Mm...

1065
00:46:52.416 --> 00:46:54.418
<i>VOIT: Do you have any idea
how many pieces</i>

1066
00:46:54.551 --> 00:46:57.821
of fan mail I get in here
every single day?

1067
00:46:57.921 --> 00:46:59.889
You know that comes
with the territory.

1068
00:46:59.989 --> 00:47:01.925
- It's messed-up.
- Well...

1069
00:47:02.759 --> 00:47:05.462
...you'll get no argument
from me there.

1070
00:47:07.564 --> 00:47:11.435
So. I guess I got it
into my head that maybe...

1071
00:47:13.237 --> 00:47:15.739
...if I got put down.
these idiots

1072
00:47:15.839 --> 00:47:19.576
would realize that
I'm not a fucking hero.

1073
00:47:20.710 --> 00:47:22.912
That wouldn't
have worked anyway.

1074
00:47:23.012 --> 00:47:24.781
No. it wouldn't.
because parasites

1075
00:47:24.914 --> 00:47:28.518
like Brian Garrity would turn
my execution into martyrdom.

1076
00:47:28.585 --> 00:47:30.587
Yeah. That's right.

1077
00:47:30.687 --> 00:47:32.155
Yeah.

1078
00:47:33.056 --> 00:47:34.858
Still my fault.

1079
00:47:36.226 --> 00:47:37.961
All the-all the lives
I've taken.

1080
00:47:38.061 --> 00:47:41.130
the network of killers
I put together. my...

1081
00:47:41.231 --> 00:47:44.401
trial. my confessions.
it's all just...

1082
00:47:45.869 --> 00:47:48.905
...evolved into...

1083
00:47:51.207 --> 00:47:53.810
...social contagion.

1084
00:48:03.487 --> 00:48:05.689
(door buzzes)

1085
00:48:06.623 --> 00:48:08.858
(indistinct chatter)

1086
00:48:13.897 --> 00:48:15.599
And while you were away...

1087
00:48:16.400 --> 00:48:18.802
...saved you a whole bunch
of fan letters.

1088
00:48:18.902 --> 00:48:21.070
(door buzzes)

1089
00:48:30.314 --> 00:48:32.516
♪ ♪

1090
00:48:50.934 --> 00:48:52.669
♪ ♪

1091
00:48:53.503 --> 00:48:55.839
<i>VOIT:
It's sad how pathetic I am.</i>

1092
00:48:55.939 --> 00:48:57.907
<i>but you know
what's even more pathetic?</i>

1093
00:48:58.675 --> 00:49:01.110
<i>Someone who makes
a show about it.</i>

1094
00:49:06.983 --> 00:49:09.353
<i>And anyone who listens to it.</i>

1095
00:49:12.956 --> 00:49:15.124
♪ ♪
